name: registry
summary: "The genepool's request-handling core — the registry API that IS known.life, mounted inside the site/ Astro Worker. `router.ts` is the one dispatch table; `routes/` holds one handler module per surface (publish · resolve · package · claim · lifecycle · maintainers · auth · mcp · setup · github-app · skill + the two OAuth bridges); `lib/` holds the shared spine every route leans on (db · blobs · scan · fit · manifest · semantic · jwt · ratelimit). This is the ~5k-LOC substance every other .life depends on: `/api/resolve/<gene>/latest` is how genes are inherited and `/api/publish` is how they are mutated back. No deploy frontmatter lives here — site/ is the deploy unit; this cell is the map of what that unit serves."

---

# registry — the genepool API

This is the genepool **as code**: the request handler every other .life talks
to. It has no `.life` deploy frontmatter of its own — the whole Worker ships as
one deployable described by `site/.life`; this cell exists to give the registry
its own map instead of burying ~30 files in the parent's census.

`src/middleware.ts` (one level up, in `site/`) forwards the dynamic genepool
paths into `router.ts`; Astro owns `/`, `/docs/*`, and the static assets.

## The shape

- **`router.ts`** — the single dispatch table. Method+path → one handler. The
  header comment is the canonical route list; `/healthz`, `/api/provides/<cap>`
  (reverse capability lookup), `/api/owner/<login>`, `/explore`, `/search`, and
  the content-negotiated `/<name>` gene page are handled inline, everything
  else delegates to `routes/`.
- **`routes/`** — one module per surface:
  - **`publish`** — the publish pipeline: auth → scan → fit → cut. The
    pre-publish secret/PII scan is *not* its own route; it runs here via
    `lib/scan.ts`.
  - **`resolve`** — the engine install endpoint (`handleResolve`) + the
    `requires:` reverse lookup (`handleProvides`). The load-bearing read path.
  - **`package`** — the public read views: gene page, `explore`, `search`,
    `owner`.
  - **`claim`** / **`lifecycle`** — name claim; deprecate · unpublish · wipe
    (the owner/admin mutate surface).
  - **`maintainers`** — account-level publish delegation (logins the owner
    trusts to publish all their genes).
  - **`auth`** + **`mcp-oauth`** + **`cloudflare-oauth`** + **`mcp`** —
    lifekey-proven challenge/prove, the MCP OAuth bridge, the Cloudflare OAuth
    onboarding bridge, and the MCP JSON-RPC server (public read surface).
  - **`github-app`** — the durable-verifier central half: one-click GitHub App
    manifest registration + `POST /exchange/verify`, the delegated nonce read
    the secrets vault calls instead of holding a GitHub credential of its own.
  - **`setup`** — the hosted cold-start flow; **`skill`** — serves the
    known.life skill markdown.
- **`lib/`** — the shared spine: `db` (D1 — accounts, names, packages,
  versions, installs, deps, embeddings), `blobs`/`files` (R2 content-addressed
  package storage), `scan` (secret/PII gate), `fit` (publish shaping),
  `manifest` (gene manifest assembly), `semantic` (Workers-AI embeddings for
  `/search`, lazy + cached), `jwt`/`cf-oauth`/`gh-secrets`/`lifekey-verify`
  (auth primitives), `ratelimit`, `config`, `id`, `types`, `pages`.

## The test seam

The credential-free vitest suite that pins this surface lives in **`site/test/`**
(`npm test`, CI job `worker-unit`) — a sibling, not under this cell, because the
tests run from the Astro package root. When you change a route or a `lib/`
helper, its test is in `site/test/<name>.test.ts`.
